What broke
1. GitHub auth was using the wrong model
The app originally relied on a personal access token flow. That caused permission problems for GitHub write actions, especially when trying to create refs and PRs.

2. GitHub App private key format was wrong
The GitHub App key had to be stored as a single-line env value with escaped newlines. Multiline formatting caused signing errors like Invalid keyData.

3. A client component imported server-only GitHub code
UpdateButton imported server-side GitHub logic directly, which broke Next.js rendering because server-only modules cannot be bundled into client

